```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Blog</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #333;
            font-size: 24px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        p {
            color: #666;
            font-size: 16px;
        }

        .article {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        .author {
            color: #999;
            font-size: 14px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="article">
        <h1>Hello World</h1>
        <p>This is my first article.</p>
        <p class="author">Author: John Doe</p>
    </div>

    <div class="article">
        <h1>Introduction to HTML</h1>
        <p>HTML is the standard markup language for creating web pages.</p>
        <p class="author">Author: Jane Smith</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```
